'''Graffiti USA''' is an American agency founded in 2011 in association with [[Klughaus Gallery]], that offers commissioned [[aerosol spray]] paint murals and artwork from a group of top professional graffiti artists.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thelodownny.com/leslog/2014/07/my-les-victor-fung.html |title=My LES: Victor Fung |publisher=The Lo Down |date=2014-07-12}}</ref> Their work includes residential and commercial interiors, business exteriors, graffiti-related set design, traditional graffiti, live artwork at events and sign painting.

==Work==

Their work is popular with young tech companies and can be seen in the offices of [[Facebook]] and [[LinkedIn]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://newyork.cbslocal.com/2014/08/06/more-and-more-new-york-city-landlords-embracing-street-art/ |title=More And More New York City Landlords Embracing Street Art |publisher=CBS New York |date=2014-08-06}}</ref> Other corporate office work includes [[MasterCard]] and [[ABC News]], which featured a Graffiti USA commissioned mural on October 8th, 2014 episode of [[Nightline]].<ref>{{cite web | url=http://abcnews.go.com/Nightline/video/watch-artists-created-nightline-graffiti-mural-26063838 | title=http://abcnews.go.com/Nightline/video/watch-artists-created-nightline-graffiti-mural-26063838| work=ABC News | date=9 Oct 2014}}</ref>

